<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 08 at 1:46PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHWESTERN WHEATLAND AND NORTH
CENTRAL SWEET GRASS COUNTIES THROUGH 215 PM MDT...
At 144 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 22
miles southwest of Harlowton, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Harlowton.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
